This is the Apache-2.0 license for most of the NovoMCP repository: the
tool wrappers (chem-props, autodock-gpu, gromacs-md, openfold3, novomcp-qm,
novomcp-nnp, and other thin adapters over open primitives), the surfaces
(frontend, Workbench, CLI, connectors), the protocol / schemas, the audit
capability, and the training recipes.

The NOVEL ORCHESTRATION CORE (the tool registry, funnel scaffolding, and
agent-loop engine — the `novomcp/mcp/` package minus its own wrappers)
is governed by a SEPARATE license: `LICENSE.core` — Business Source
License 1.1 with a change date of 2029-07-12 to Apache-2.0. This split
protects against cloud-provider re-hosting of the core while the OSS
project establishes itself, and converts to fully permissive on the
change date. See `LICENSE.core` for the full terms.

The FAVES framework paper (published separately on ChemRxiv) is licensed
CC-BY-NC-ND 4.0. That license does NOT apply to any code in this
repository; it governs only the manuscript.
